# Multi-Session Chat History — Implementation Plan

## Codebase Summary (What I Found)

| Layer | File | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| Entry point | [main.py](file:///f:/medical-agent/main.py) | FastAPI app, lifespan startup, CORS, serves `static/index.html` |
| Routes | [routes.py](file:///f:/medical-agent/api/routes.py) | `POST /api/chat` (text) + `POST /api/lab-upload` (file). Uses `ChatRequest(query: str)` and `ChatResponse(response, tool_used)` |
| Agent | [agent.py](file:///f:/medical-agent/agent/agent.py) | `run_agent(query: str)` builds `[HumanMessage(content=query)]` and calls `agent.invoke({"messages": [...]})`. No history today. |
| Frontend | [index.html](file:///f:/medical-agent/static/index.html) | Single-file HTML (1013 lines). Dark theme, sidebar shows tool cards (not sessions). Chat bubbles with markdown rendering. |
| Config | [.env](file:///f:/medical-agent/.env) | `GROQ_API_KEY`, `OPENAI_API_KEY`, `NCBI_API_KEY`, `ANONYMIZED_TELEMETRY` |
| Deps | [requirements.txt](file:///f:/medical-agent/requirements.txt) | FastAPI, LangChain, Groq, etc. No SQLite dependency needed (it's in Python stdlib). |

**Key observations:**
- The current `/api/chat` is stateless — each request creates a fresh `[HumanMessage]` and sends it to the agent. No history is maintained.
- `run_agent()` accepts a `query: str` and internally builds the `messages` list. This function needs a **new signature** to accept pre-built messages.
- The sidebar currently shows only static tool cards (Symptoms, Drug, Lab). It needs to be restructured to also show session history.
- SQLite is in Python's standard library — **no new pip dependency is needed**.

