> [!IMPORTANT]
> **User ID strategy**: Since there is no authentication system, I will hardcode `user_id = "default_user"` in the frontend. All sessions belong to one user. If you want multi-user support later, this can be replaced with a login system — the DB schema already supports it via the `user_id` column.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Database location**: The SQLite file will be created at `data/sessions.db`. This keeps it alongside other data files. Let me know if you prefer a different location.

> [!IMPORTANT]  
> **Lab upload sessions**: The `POST /api/lab-upload` endpoint will NOT be session-aware in this implementation (it currently bypasses the agent entirely and calls the lab tool directly). Lab upload results will appear in the chat UI but won't be persisted to session history. Let me know if you want this included too.

